column3: Thanks Nathaniel for always keeping my long run avg down

First super hot day, 94 when we started. So quick water stops 3 times but this was a good run nonetheless! You know me and Madi are about to get those 64 ounce polar pops now 
Update: polar pop received

Greenbelt to trails today, picked it up the last couple miles but not as fast as I wish I could have. Saw 2 baby coyotes on the back side of Bertha and they were incredibly cute. I was scared that their mama was gonna pop out from hiding but all is good— no confrontation, didn’t get mauled, just got to see so adorable wildlife

Went by feel again, only listened for watch beeps to know what mile I was at and it worked out well again. Never listen to music when running outside, but did today for whatever reason— looking back I know that the fastest mile was definitely when Truth Hurts played. Not surprised at all. What a glorious song. 
+ 8 strides

@ 75%
Definitely needed to take it slow today

WU, 6x1600 w/ 2-2:30 jog rest, 400 at end. Splits were 6:47, 6:48, 6:45, 6:48, 6:07, 6:30, 78
Miles alternated between track and grass. Did the first 4 w/ varsity DV girls. Felt really good like I could do that pace all day. Wanted to pick it up for the last two but I didn’t have a number in mind so that’s why that 6:07 happened (oops), which ended up being a bit too aggressive because I felt it on that last grass one. Still happy with this because I think it’s evidence of hard work paying off (especially strides lmao, thank god).
Followed by 6 strides
